<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871207-0153 </DOCNO><HL> ATI's Board Retains Adviser</HL><DD> 12/07/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ATIM </IN><DATELINE> GLENDALE, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   ATI Medical Inc. said its board retained Shearson Lehman Brothers Inc. to help explore a possible sale of the company or other alternatives &quot;for optimizing shareholders' values.&quot;    ATI, which rents medical equipment to hospitals, said alternatives include merger, raising capital by issuing equity or debt or selling assets.    Although ATI said it has been discussing these alternatives, it declined to identify with whom it had discussed them, and it said &quot;there is no assurance that any transactions will be consummated in the immediate future.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>